Description: TIEC provides assistance in the development, implementation and maintenance of Quality Management Systems in compliance.
Full Description: Texas International Engineering Consultants (TIEC) provides assistance through advice and interpretation in the development, implementation and maintenance of Quality Management Systems in compliance with a variety of industry standards (such as API Q1, API Q2, ISO 9001, ISO 14001, and OHSAS 18001) leading to system compliance, certification and/or licensing to enhance the organization’s market share. TIEC also provides competent source/vendor auditors, HSSE auditors, source inspectors and pipeline inspectors to assure customer and regulatory requirements are achieved and maintained. TIEC has extensive international experience working with large and small manufacturers and service companies worldwide. TIEC International maintains an office in Singapore to directly service the Asian market. TIEC was established in 2000 to provide consulting, auditing, training, source inspection, and special process qualifications for the development, implementation and improvement of quality management systems. Additionally, TIEC offers customized training for Quality, Risk Assessment, Leadership, Safety, Environmental compliance and many other topics. With over 300 years combined experience, TIEC’s staff are dedicated to delivering services customized to its clients’ needs by providing hands-on approach to ensure the client receives practical, cost effective, real-world training, consulting, auditing and inspection services using trained and competent personnel. The management team is involved in our industry with over 60 years working on API Committees, such as API Q1, API Q2, API 5L, API 5CT, SC5, SC20, SC18 and more. They have been Chairmen of API Task Groups and Work Groups, have been API Auditors, API Senior Auditors, API Trainers, API Master Trainers, API Practitioners, and they are IRCA, and Exemplar Global Certified Auditors and more. TIEC is qualified and competent to assist your QMS and inspection needs to reduce potential nonproductive time, reduce your overall cost of quality and promote continual improvement for your business worldwide.

Description: ivLessons is an online marketplace that enables its users to provide or obtain tutoring services.
Full Description: ivLessons, an abbreviation for Internet Video Lessons, is an Internet education service company providing online 1-on-1 or group lessons and webcasting live lectures using online video conferencing.  They are distinguished by the implemented API and number of students participating simultaneously.   1. Lessons  -Participating Students: one-on-one or up to 4 students per a teacher  -Video Streaming: Peer-to-Peer direct video and audio communication between the two users using Web-RTC protocol. High Definition video quality is available with minimum latency that is superior to any other video streaming technology.   -Virtual Whiteboard: Participants can draw, word process, chat and upload various files for instructions.   -Compatible Web Browsers: Internet Explorer, Google Chrome and Mozilla Firefox 2. Lectures  -Limitless participants  -Text chatting capacity for communication between teachers and students when lecturing   -Unidirectional video streaming broadcasting based on Adobe Flash  -Wowza Streaming Engine for media server  -Amazon Cloud Front, EC2 Server Instances enabling automatic load balancing on video traffic distribution -Compatible with most major web browsers including Microsoft Internet Explorer, Apple Safari, Google Chrome and Mozilla Firefox 3. Operations ivLessons.com is an online Educational Open Market.  Teachers can, after approval from ivLessons through evaluating college transcripts and criminal background check, freely list their lessons and lectures that includes title, profile, brief introduction and price set by their own.  Subsequently, ivLessons promotes the teachers and their teaching subjects to students mainly based on online marketing. Teachers and students will log into either Lessons Room or Lecture Viewer on our website at a prearranged Time using our web applications. There is no limit for subjects. Though the subject areas are categorized by Language, Mathematics, Science, Music, Test Preparation, Technology and Miscellaneous. 4. Company ivLessons USA, LLC was founded in Houston, Texas, February 2012, which controls all business operations in north America. ivLessons Co., Ltd was later established and headquartered in Seoul, Korea in January 2014 that takes full control of Asian market including Korea, Japan and China.  All web applications developed so far have been outsourced to multiple Indian web developers under the strict supervision of the company’s president and founder, Dr. Jinseung Han. He is a Doctor of Education in Music, awarded by Columbia University, New York. He had been a professor for 15 years teaching music composition and music technology at colleges and universities for both undergraduate and graduate levels.

Buyers can even interact with the dealers and begin negotiations. HKS Media Group weeds out tire kickers and gives dealers access to serious buyers who want to buy now. HKS Media Group was founded on the idea of making the practice of buying and selling a vehicle a much more stress free and efficient process – both for the buyer and the dealer. Description: Asmacure Ltée develops proprietary compounds that target cholinergic receptors for the treatment of pulmonary airway diseases.
Full Description: Asmacure Ltée is a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company focused on the development of novel, proprietary compounds that target cholinergic receptors for the treatment of inflammation, notably pulmonary airway diseases. The company’s lead compound, ASM-024, has a novel multi-functional mechanism of action with nicotinic and muscarinic effects. ASM-024 has demonstrated the capabilities of anti-inflammation, bronchoprotection, and smooth muscle relaxation in pre-clinical asthma models. Administered as a solution for nebulization in asthma patients, ASM-024 demonstrated clinical proof of concept in a phase 2 trial with significant effects on FEV1 and methacholine PC20. Asmacure has advanced ASM-024 into the clinic for the treatment of moderate asthma and COPD with a dry powder for inhalation (DPI) formulation. The DPI is a preferred dosage form for many patients and should allow ASM-024 to be delivered with greater lung deposition yielding the potential for a lower and more optimal dose. Asmacure was founded by Dr. Yvon Cormier, a noted pulmonologist, and Dr Evelyne Israel-Assayag in 2002 and is based in Quebec City, Quebec, Canada.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering

Full Description: First published in August 2002 by T & L Publications, Inc as a supplement to Nuts & Volts Magazine called "The Nuts & Volts of Amateur Robotics." SERVO Magazine is dedicated to the "Next Generation of Robotics Experimenters", devoted 100% to robots and robotics. With an all robots - all the time focus, each monthly issue will inspire, educate, and entertain with feature articles, interviews, tutorials, DIY projects, hacks, parts sources and much more. Whether you are building your first line-follower or finishing off the perception layer in a positronic brain, SERVO Magazine delivers the sharp technical tools you need to stay on the cutting edge. Advances in robotics are dynamic and as important as those of computers in the 80s and 90s. Topics are diverse and range from programmable logic, stepping motor basics, radio communication basics for robots, autonomous operation, closed loop systems, voice recognition, adding vision, bit banging, to product and book reviews, and build-it-yourself bots and systems projects. Events such as DARPA, robot soccer championships, FIRST, ComBots, underwater robot challenges, just to name a few are covered, as well.
